&gt; Can a capturing group value be used in the definition of another capturing group?

generally speaking - yes. you can write your own pattern compilation logic to support such feature.

is this feature supported by Jdk - no (afaik).

also you need to keep in mind a **type** of the back reference - its `char[]`, not a `number`. thus `\\w{\\1}` would require some non-trivial assumptions or explicit type conversion syntax.

also while keeping in mind back reference **type**, you can make quite tricky manipulations, e.g.:

```
