What about `%n` using a formatter like **`String.format()`**?:

    String s = String.format(&quot;I%nam%na%nboy&quot;);

As [this answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/209771/3998458) says, its available from java 1.5 and is another way to `System.getProperty(&quot;line.separator&quot;)` or `System.lineSeparator()` and, like this two, is **OS independent**.

